creator: Anna Matlack Richards
description: LibriVox recording of A New Alice in the Old Wonderland by Anna Matlack Richards.  Read in English by CJ Plog. In this unofficial sequel to Alice in Wonderland and Through the Looking-/Glass, a different Alice, a young American girl named Alice Lee (who adores the original books), stumbles upon a magical door that leads to Wonderland. There, she meets familiar faces, like the Cheshire Cat, Mad Hatter, Red Queen, among others, as well as some new ones. However, unlike our beloved English Alice who just tries to make sense of a senseless world, Alice Lee maintains power over her own fantasy, rather than let herself become the victim. Though a loving tribute to the original novels, Lewis Carroll absolutely disapproved of the book, nearly seeking legal action against the British publication of it, but decided against it in favor of his privacy and reputation. (Mary Kay and Carolin Sigler) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.  For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
